17 are physically present, means have been afforded for the public to have simultaneous
18 access to the teleconference meeting:
19 (A) Development authorities created pursuant to or authorized by the provisions of
20 Chapter 42 or Chapter 62 of Title 36, by or pursuant to Article IX, Section VI,
21 Paragraph III of the Georgia Constitution, or by or pursuant to any amendment to the
22 Constitution continued pursuant to the authority of Article XI, Section I, Paragraph IV
23 of the Constitution;
24 (B) Community improvement districts created pursuant to the provisions of Article IX,
25 Section VII of the Georgia Constitution;
26 (C) Hospital authorities created pursuant to Article 4 of Chapter 7 of Title 31; and
27 (D) The board of trustees or other governing body of any large retirement system as
28 such term is defined in subsection (a) of Code Section 47-20-84;
29 (E) The board of trustees of any county or regional public library created pursuant to
30 Part 2 of Article 2 of Chapter 5 of Title 20; and
31 (F) Community service boards created pursuant to Article 1 of Chapter 2 of Title 37.
32 (2) The participation by teleconference of members of such bodies or committees thereof
33 means full participation in the same manner as if such members were physically present.
34 In the event such teleconference meeting is a public hearing, and if fewer than a quorum
35 of the members of a body or committee thereof are physically present, then members of
36 the public shall be afforded the means to participate fully in the same manner as if such
37 members of the public were physically present."
38 SECTION 2.
39 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
